The paper deals with inconsistency measures in probabilistic expert systems, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the Shapley value, which is a concept from game theory and can be categorized under knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.KR). The paper also touches upon the use of formal methods to analyze probabilistic knowledge bases, which can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
